13. Glossary
Term	Definition
Adjudication	The process by which a payer reviews and decides on a claim‚Äôs payment status.
Allowed Amount	The maximum payment a plan will allow for a covered service.
Capitation	Payment arrangement where providers are paid a set amount per patient per period.
Coinsurance	The percentage of costs of a covered health care service paid by the patient.
CPT Code	Current Procedural Terminology; standard for medical procedures.
Denial	A claim or service not approved for payment by the payer.
EDI	Electronic Data Interchange; file format standard for claims submission.
NPI	National Provider Identifier.
Remittance Advice	Explanation of payments made by a payer to a provider.
...	...
